SIMPLE: disciplinable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disciplinable
<hw>Dis"ci*plin*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>disciplinable</ets>. See <er>Discipline</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being disciplined or improved by instruction and
training.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Liable or deserving to be disciplined; subject to
disciplinary punishment; <as>as, a <ex>disciplinable</ex>
offense</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disciplinableness</ent>⟦br⟧
